  "prompt": "How can I become a detective in India?",
  "response": "To become a detective in India, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Educational Qualifications\n- Minimum 10+2 or graduate degree\n- Preferably in disciplines like criminology, law, forensic science, or criminal justice\n\n2. Age Requirements\n- Typically between 21-35 years old\n- May vary slightly depending on the specific agency or department\n\n3. Career Paths\na) Government Detective Agencies\n- Join police services through:\n  - UPSC Civil Services Exam (IPS)\n  - State Police Service Exams\n  - Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) recruitment\n\nb) Private Detective Agencies\n- Complete required training\n- Obtain necessary licenses from state authorities\n- Gain experience through internships or entry-level positions\n\n4. Skills Required\n- Strong analytical and observation skills\n- Good communication\n- Physical fitness\n- Problem-solving abilities\n- Knowledge of law and investigation techniques\n\n5. Training\n- Police training academies\n- Specialized investigation courses\n- Forensic science training\n- Private detective training programs\n\n6. Licensing\n- Obtain private detective license from state government\n- Meet specific eligibility criteria\n- Clear background verification\n\nRecommended additional steps include learning foreign languages, developing computer skills, and staying updated with modern investigation techniques.",
